Commercial & Legal is equipped to provide the full range of Property and Commercial Law services required by its clients in both a commercial and residential capacity, including Commercial and Corporate Law, Building and Construction Law, Residential Conveyancing, and Estate Planning and Administration. 

My key responsibilities at Commercial & Legal have included: 
– Completing general office tasks as a rounds clerk;
– Liaising and assisting lawyers in the firm by undertaking various tasks;
– Undertaking legal research;
– Preparing, drafting and reviewing legal documents/forms (mainly property) and letters;
– Preparing and assisting in the signing and witnessing of wills;
– Becoming familiar with the LEAP legal practice management software.

The Office of the Director of Public Prosecutions provides an effective, fair and independent criminal prosecution service for the people of South Australia. The Office is committed to the highest ethical and professional standards and strives to achieve the most effective and appropriate criminal prosecutions.

Having previously worked in various defence law firms, the ODPP exposed me to "the other side", that being the prosecution. I gained invaluable experience working a long side highly respected prosecutors.

Key Responsibilities:
– Assisted prosecutors with legal research involving major indictable criminal matters;  
– Assisted prosecutors by drafting and reviewing legal documents in preparation of trial; 
– Attended court with prosecutors and observed court proceedings;
– Attended and observed the process of 'proofing' witnesses in preparation of trial;
– Completed general administrative tasks; Reading files and becoming familiar with prosecution forms and statements involving major indictable matters.

