•	This role covers a variety of claims, including property damage and bodily injury, with a focus on construction claims;
•	Managing claims handling enquiries including but not limited to coverage determination, quantum analysis and legal liability assessment, where appropriate and within authority limits;
•	Timely determination of claims in accordance with company policies, industry standards and applicable legislation;
•	Managing claims using the appropriate external and internal specialists to achieve effective and efficient settlement outcomes;
•	Timely and accurate input, processing, authorisation and payment of claims;
•	Proper documentation of claims processing and outcomes;
•	Manage complaints as per QBE Insurance company guidelines and Industry best practice; 
•	Negotiation of claims settlements including running Informal Settlement Conferences without appointing external Counsel on unlitigated matters and low quantum litigated matters; 
•	A continuing improvement, focus and attitude towards implementation of new work practices and procedures, initiating and facilitating change and innovations;
•	Ensuring the delivery of the highest quality customer service and developing strong working relationships with all customers and service providers; and 
•	Reporting in accordance with relevant company service standards and manuals.

•	Supervision and mentoring of an employed solicitor and business partner;
•	Drafting commercial contracts for companies, such as deeds of assignment, employment agreements, shareholder agreements, company constitutions, trust deeds amongst others; 
•	Registering Trademarks for companies and providing legal advice on how best to protect the exclusive rights of directors and the company to the Trademark;  
