•	Drafting Co-ownership deeds for individuals who own a property as a tenancy in common; 
•	Resolving Co-ownership disputes through mediation without the need to proceed to court; 
•	Registering a Liquor Licence for commercial premises and ensuring the premises is fully compliant with Liquor Licence regulations and Council Development Consent for the service of alcohol;  
•	Assisting clients to informally resolve neighbourhood disputes;   
•	 Resolving debt recovery matters against our client informally through payment plan agreements with the creditor and averting costly NSW Civil and Administrative Tribunal (NCAT) hearings;  
•	Perusing and advising on different types of commercial and construction contracts so that the client is fully aware of their rights and obligations under such contracts; and 
•	Attendance and appearance at NCAT, Local Court, District Court & Supreme Court in relation to various types of civil disputes.

•	Providing comprehensive, detailed and succinct legal advice on complex policy indemnity issues, public liability, product liability, professional indemnity and property damage matters to Zurich Insurance, QBE Insurance and CGU Recoveries; 
•	Drafting Consent Judgements/Orders, Calderbank offers, Offers of Compromise, Defences, Statements of Claim, Cross claims, Notice of Motion and other court documentation;
•	Appearances at the Local, District and Supreme Court for mentions, pre-trial conferences and directions hearings; 
•	Demonstrated ability to brief appropriate liability and medical experts;
•	Ability to strategically consider the best way forward in a matter in order to reach an early commercial resolution and avoid incurring unnecessary legal costs for the client; 
•	Running Informal Settlement Conferences and achieving commercial outcomes desired by the client; 
•	Attendance at the insured’s premises to supervise a view and protect the insured's interests in the matter; 
•	Preparing a matter for hearing, including comprehensive briefs to junior and/or senior counsel; and 
•	Attendance at in-house CPD seminars to assist in developing my legal skills/knowledge and ensuring they are up-to-date and relevant.

•	Pro-active management of a wide variety of high quantum public & product liability, property damage & personal injury claims across all Australian/International jurisdictions;
•	Ensuring that my portfolio of claims is reserved in accordance with the relevant reserving philosophy set by the Australian Insurance Industry;
•	Liaising with third parties, investigators, as well as an extensive national legal panel;
•	Analysis of the Liability/risk issues arising from individual claims, with multiple contributing parties;
•	Drafting correspondence addressing policy analysis and policy coverage; 
•	Attendance at mediation's and provided instructions to Lawyers regarding commercial settlement and overall legal strategy for settlement of complex claims; 
•	Demonstrated ability to strategically resolve large loss property damage claims exceeding $5,000,000 in claim & legal costs; 
•	Facilitated structured and regular contact with clients to resolve high risk & complex matters; 
•	Analysis of the liability risk exposure of our insured, particularly in complex dual insurance claims where our insured had taken out multiple policies with different insurers for the same policy period; and
•	Demonstrated ability to reconcile international claims payments with local claims, through the Zurich IPZ system.

•	Ownership and management of a portfolio of public/product liability & property damage incidents and claims, liaising with relevant parties, assessing liability and financial exposure and making recommendations for the future legal strategy of each claim, whilst achieving a superior result for clients;
•	Communicated effectively with claimants, clients, brokers, investigators, lawyers, insurers and medical practitioners via written and verbal means;
•	Demonstrated effective negotiation and liaison techniques with clients, claimants, lawyers, brokers, insurers and service providers for public liability insurance claims across Australia;
•	Managed the incidents and claims accounts for a number of corporate clients including, Mirvac, Retpro, Bayton, Priceline, Scott & Broad, Charter Hall, Lend Lease, Costco and all Australian Airports. 
•	Provided training, as required, to the insured to facilitate improved risk management;
•	Reported to and updated relevant stakeholders regarding claims as required;
•	Facilitated regular and structured contact with clients; 
•	Thorough understanding of insurance policy, application and policy coverage; 
•	Utilised marketing and networking opportunities to expand Proclaims business opportunities;
•	Supported other team members as required through training and guidance on complex claims;
•	Conducted Informal Queensland proceedings under the Personal Injuries Proceedings Act 2002 (QLD) within the insured’s excess and was able to negotiate with a number of respondents to reach a mutually beneficial settlement outcome; 
•	Drafted and served contribution notices under various state legislation on a number of companies, where there was an issue of joint liability. For example, cleaning companies, security companies and Centre/club management companies; and
•	Interpreted the terms and provisions of a variety of contracts, including cleaning and management agreements for a number of different entities.

•	Completed conveyancing files from start to finish, including preparing the contract for the vendor and carrying out the initial title searches as well as explaining the contract to the purchaser; 
•	Carried out title searches, prepared the transfer of title and raised requisitions on the title with the vendor’s solicitor; 
•	Prepared the settlement adjustment sheet based on the searches from authorities such as the office of state revenue, water providers, councils as well as other authorities;
•	Settled property matters at SAI global, banks and vendors solicitors offices; 
•	Attended court and carried out mentions and hearings for both civil and criminal matters; 
•	Handled a number of debt recovery matters, namely in the area of CTP motor vehicle claims and personal injury matters;  
•	Liased with barristers on complicated civil and criminal litigation matters, speaking to them directly over the phone and preparing written briefs that articulate the nature and stage of the matter;
•	Drafted debt recovery contracts as well as contracts for the delivery and supply of goods between businesses and individuals; 
•	Interpreted the provisions of complex building and commercial contracts, providing advice to clients using simple language that is not legalese; 
•	Prepared and filed divorce applications in the Federal Circuit Court for complicated family matters involving child maintenance, spousal maintenance and property disputes; and 
•	Carried out multiple divorce directions hearings at the Federal Circuit Court.

•	Prepared personal injury and property damage claims arising from motor vehicle accidents; 
•	Carried out Debt Recovery Litigation from insurance companies on behalf of the plaintiff in accordance with the civil litigation rules and procedures in the small and general claims divisions of the Local Court;
•	Prepared and sent by email Letters of Demand to the at-fault insurer and also sent offers of compromise to the at-fault insurer by email and over the telephone, in order to negotiate a settlement and avoid civil litigation; 
•	Prepared Personal Injury Claims for clients, including the application form, medical documents and negotiated a settlement figure with the Motor Accidents Authority; 
•	Liaised with a diversity of different clients from an array of backgrounds and socio-economic circumstances regarding their motor vehicle accident claims; 
•	Attended court and carried out mentions, setting the hearing date for a matter, setting the date for exchange of evidence and or issuing a subpoena to produce documents on the defendant;
•	Drafted Statements and Affidavits for matters in the small and general claims divisions of the local court; 
•	Prepared and filed statements of claim, defenses and default judgment through the Local Court online registry; and
•	Attended to a number of telephone calls and negotiated with insurance companies, clients, defendant’s solicitors and vehicle repairers in order to reach a mutually beneficial settlement amount and avoid litigation.

•	Engaged in face-to-face conferences with clients and completed/lodged Immigration Applications forms for Protection visas, Student visas, Visitor visas, Carer Visas, Spouse visas and Employer Nomination Scheme 457 visas;
•	Conducted face-to-face conferences with clients in order to ascertain the key legal issues pertaining to their migration status within Australia and abroad; 
•	Prepared Briefs for Barristers regarding complicated immigration law class-actions in the Federal Circuit Court and High Court.
•	 Drafted statements of claim and affidavits, in order to initiate appeals to the Federal Circuit Court within 28 days of an unfavorable decision made by either the Refugee Review Tribunal, Migration Review Tribunal and or the Federal Immigration Minister;  
•	 Informed clients as to the exact stage and progress of their matter either face-to-face or over the telephone; and
•	 Attended to a number of telephone calls with clients, Department of Immigration case officers, Tribunal members, Federal Circuit Court registry officers & Barristers.

•	Working directly with the solicitor on generalist areas of law, relating to credit card scams, traffic offences, third party insurance claims, bankruptcy, family divorce settlements and minor assaults;
•	Drafting statements of claim and affidavits for clients in both civil and criminal matters; 
•	Observing and taking notes, while the solicitor is advising and instructing the client; 
•	Assisting the solicitor to attain the facts and legal issues of the client’s case, by asking specific questions relating to the clients situation;
•	Writing letters to clients advising the client of the requirements and process of their case in a team setting, under the instructions of the practicing solicitor;
•	Contacting clients on the phone in order to prepare a summarised brief for the solicitor of their particular case; and
•	Observing court proceedings at the Parramatta Local Court, including minor assaults, traffic offences, family disputes, breach of AVO orders and various other civil matters.

